                            <comment id="13492444" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 15:56:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=alley&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;alley&quot;&gt;alley&lt;/a&gt; would you mind verifying this Patch? Just to be sure that i didn&apos;t miss one Controller.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While changing all those Files, i already that it would be good to have one central place holding kind of a core-pattern .. will try to change that as well, if that patch is okay&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13492465" author="alley" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 16:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your prompt action on this. I have tried the patch, but patching my existing 4.0 installation (as downloaded from the website) was a little troublesome, as those files that the patch indicated as being in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;solr/webapp/web/js/scripts&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;are actually under:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;solr-webapp/webapp/js/scripts&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in my installation. Replacing the paths in the patch and applying it, however, worked, and the web gui seems to work w/o issues. (I had however to open the web gui in another browser, as mine seemed to have cached all those js and refused to reload them unless I refreshed them one by one).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13492475" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 16:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;as those files that the patch indicated as being in:&lt;br/&gt;
solr/webapp/web/js/scripts&lt;br/&gt;
are actually under:&lt;br/&gt;
solr-webapp/webapp/js/scripts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in &lt;tt&gt;solr/webapp/web&lt;/tt&gt; the source-files are located, where as in &lt;tt&gt;example/solr-webapp/webapp&lt;/tt&gt; your running instance is holding their copies of the source-files&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But anyway, fine that it works &amp;#8211; will work on the second version with a global corename-pattern to make these changes in the feature a bit easier&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Allesandro!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
